              What was the central lesson of "Jill's Birthday"?
            ]]></mattext>
          </material>
          <response_lid ident="response_q2" rcardinality="Single">
            <render_choice shuffle="No">
              <response_label ident="q2_a">
                <material><mattext texttype="text/plain">Bigger parties are always better</mattext></material>
              </response_label>
              <response_label ident="q2_b">
                <material><mattext texttype="text/plain">Love isn't about grand gestures but understanding</mattext></material>
              </response_label>
              <response_label ident="q2_c">
                <material><mattext texttype="text/plain">Tool Time should celebrate birthdays</mattext></material>
              </response_label>
              <response_label ident="q2_d">
                <material><mattext texttype="text/plain">Tim should always plan parties</mattext></material>
              </response_label>
            </render_choice>
          </response_lid>
        </presentation>

        <resprocessing>
          <outcomes>
            <decvar minvalue="0" maxvalue="100" varname="SCORE" vartype="Decimal"/>
          </outcomes>
          <respcondition title="correct" continue="No">
            <conditionvar>
              <varequal respident="response_q2">q2_b</varequal>
            </conditionvar>
            <setvar action="Set" varname="SCORE">100</setvar>
            <displayfeedback feedbacktype="Response" linkrefid="q2_correct_fb"/>
          </respcondition>
          <respcondition title="incorrect" continue="No">
            <conditionvar>
              <other/>
            </conditionvar>
            <setvar action="Set" varname="SCORE">0</setvar>
            <displayfeedback feedbacktype="Response" linkrefid="q2_incorrect_fb"/>
          </respcondition>
        </resprocessing>

        <itemfeedback ident="q2_correct_fb">
          <material>
            <mattext texttype="text/html"><![CDATA[
              <strong>Simple is better!</strong><br/>
              Tim's "improvements" to Jill's birthday threatened to overshadow the simple things she actually wanted. A perfect encapsulation of Tim's character: good intentions, excessive execution, eventual realization.
            ]]></mattext>
          </material>
        </itemfeedback>
        <itemfeedback ident="q2_incorrect_fb">
          <material>
            <mattext texttype="text/html"><![CDATA[
              <strong>Deeper meaning!</strong><br/>
              The correct answer is <em>Love isn't about grand gestures but understanding</em>. Tim learned that Jill wanted simplicity, not spectacle.
            ]]></mattext>
          </material>
        </itemfeedback>
      </item>

